06-01-14","FULLY MODDED PHPBB 2 OFFICIAL DOCUMENTATION","","","Advertise with Us Need to attract new business and customers? Have your website banner placed in rotation on the Fully Modded phpBB website for a small monthly fee. All online transactions are safe and secured. 468px x 60px : 20/month per banner 88px x 31px : 10/month per banner Any Restrictions? We don \'t allow adult or other \'disreputable \' sites to advertise. Acceptable banner image formats are .jpg, .jpeg, .gif, .png, .bmp, and .swf. All advertisements will be screened and we reserve the right to reject any advertisement we find unacceptable to our audience. All prices are in US Dollars You may cancel your advertising at any time Partial months will not be refunded Once payment is made please e-mail me a copy of your banner url, url for the hyperlink, and alt text details.",3),array(30,"service_custom.html","2006-01-14","FULLY MODDED PHPBB 2 OFFICIAL DOCUMENTATION","","","Custom Installations / Upgrades Take the worry out of setting up your board, applying a new upgrade, or adding a few mods. Allow us to do it all for you so you can focus on more important site matters. All online transactions are safe and secured. Fully Modded New Installation : 20/board Fully Modded Update : 20/board phpBB to Fully Modded Update : 20/board phpBB MOD Installations : 30/hour Fully Modded MOD Installations : 35/hour PHP / MySQL Debugging : 45/hour All prices based on an hourly rate and in US Dollars. Minumum one (1) hour up-front payment. Please allow 24hrs to be contacted about your custom install/upgrade.",2),array(31,"service_hosting.html","2006-03-16","FULLY MODDED PHPBB 2 OFFICIAL DOCUMENTATION","","","Website Hosting All our plans are priced annually, setup fee free, and include Web Mail Access, Spam Assasian E-mail Protection, Frontpage Extensions, Custom Error Docs, cPanel Control Panel, phpMyAdmin, Webstats, Fantastico Auto Installer, and the server is customized specifically for Fully Modded boards. Please e-mail me if you are interested in obtaining a hosting plan. Basic Economy E-Commerce Professional Max Annual Charge 29.95 (USD) 59.95 (USD) 199.95 (USD) 239.95 (USD) 299.95 (USD) Monthly Data Transfer 1 GB 3 GB 7 GB 15 GB 30 GB Disk Storage 150 MB 300 MB 600 MB 1200 MB 2400 MB Control Panel Sub Domains 5 10 Unlimited Unlimited Unlimited Parked Domains 2 5 Unlimited Unlimited Unlimited Add-on Domains 1 5 10 15 WebMail E-mail Accounts 30 60 100 Unlimited Unlimited SMTP/POP3 E-mail Forwarding Auto Responders E-mail Aliasing Catch All E-mail Spam Assassin Mailing Lists CGI Perl PHP5 MySQL MySQL Databases 2 10 Unlimited Unlimited Unlimited phpMyAdmin Shopping Cart Fantastico Frontpage Analog Web Stats Webalizer Web Stats Unlimited FTP",16),array(32,"theme_create.html","2005-11-25","FULLY MODDED PHPBB 2 OFFICIAL DOCUMENTATION","","","Create a New Theme Creating a style for Fully Modded phpBB 2 based on the default is very easy. Follow the steps below and you \'ll have a new theme on your board within minutes. This tutorial will help you create your own styles so that they are compatible with Fully Modded phpBB 2. Each section is split in to sub sections. To make a new style you will need a few tools to make the job easier, we recommend the following: Text Editor - e.g. WordPad, EmEditor , or PHP Coder . Graphics Program - e.g. Adobe Photoshop , Paintshop Pro , Gimp , or Fireworks (Photoshop is highly recommended). i. Renaming &amp; Editing Files First, make a copy of the subSilver/ directory located in the templates/ directory. Make sure the subSilver directory that you copy is in its \' original state and has not been modified or altered at all. If you are not sure of this, then I suggest downloading it again to be safe. Copy the subSilver/ directory into the templates/ directory creating a duplicate (it should be called \'Copy of subSilver \'). Rename the copied directory to whatever your new template name is going to be, for this example our theme will be named FullyModded . Next, we need to rename the two (2) main style files, the stylesheet and the image configuration file. subSilver.cfg rename to FullyModded.cfg subSilver.css rename to FullyModded.css Next, we need to edit four (4) files in the new FullyModded/ directory and find all references of \'subSilver \', changing them all to our new template name, \'FullyModded \'. If you have a find and replace tool this is a good time to use it; you must replace \'subSilver \' with your new template name, e.g. FullyModded. prillian/prefs_tabs.tpl FullyModded.css radio.php theme_info.cfg Note: Replace the word \'FullyModded \' with your actual template name. Directory name and all filenames are case sensitive, so \'FullyModded \', \'Fullymodded \', \'fullyModded \', and \'fullymodded \' are not the same and when following the renaming instructions above you should make sure you have correct filename case everywhere. ii. Image Creation Creating any extra images for your new style can be an easy process providing you have the right software. To create images you can either: Download the subSilver SDK from phpBB and change the colours of the images. Use a software package such as Adobe Photoshop and make you own images based on what you want your style to look like. iii. Changing the Layout Changing the layout of your style can be very complex or very easy depending on how much you know about HTML and css. You could seperate the categories which are shown here or you could make your own header. The best way to this is in Dreamweaver by using these steps: Open a blank HTML document and erase everything in the code section. Open \'templates/FullyModded/overall_header.tpl \' and copy what \'s in it and paste it in the code section on the blank HTML document. Open \'templates/FullyModded/index_body.tpl \' and copy what \'s in it and paste it below the overall_header code in the code section on the blank HTML document. Open \'templates/FullyModded/overall_footer.tpl \' and copy what \'s in it and paste it below the index_body code in the code section on the blank HTML document. Go back to the HTML document and right-click on the design view, then goto CSS Styles, then Attach Style Sheet, then find your-new-template-name.css and attach it to your document, then find formIE.css and attach that to your document. Now you should be able to see how your style looks like now it has the css on it. iv. Viewing Finished Products Login as an Administrator, go to Admin - Styles &amp; Templates - Add New. If you see your new style in the list of available styles to install then you did everything correctly. You can install the style and edit it. If you don \'t see your new style in that list then you did something incorrectly (probably forgot to edit theme_info.cfg or forgot to rename subSilver.cfg ) Or, you could install both an Apache server and Fully Modded phpBB locally on your machine and have a live view of you style or you could view it the Dreamweaver way which is stated above. Disclaimer This theme tutorial is complied from tutorials from LimitDesigns , and CyberAlien , and has been modified and adapted to Fully Modded phpBB (FM2017.4.05+).",5),array(33,"theme_faq.html","2005-11-25","FULLY MODDED PHPBB 2 OFFICIAL DOCUMENTATION","","","Theme FAQ This is a very basic Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) section which attempts to answer some of the more commonly asked theme questions. Our thanks to all those people who \'ve converted themes, beta tested, contributed bug reports and code fixes in the past. Template- make_filename(): Error - file does not exist! This error is usually caused by a template file that has not uploaded to your server correctly, and as such is missing or incomplete. This error can also be caused by trying to use a theme that is not compatible with your Fully Modded version. Re-upload the missing file again, or please check the themes that you are using are compatible with the version of Fully Modded phpBB that you are using. Can I install/use phpBB 2 themes? You can not use alternative phpBB templates for Fully Modded, you should note they will not function correctly with your Fully Modded phpBB board. It is therefore recommended you only use themes available on our website that are compatible with the version that you are using. Themes downloaded from 3rd party sites are not supported by us.",1),array(34,"theme_lang_submit.html","2005-11-25","FULLY MODDED PHPBB 2 OFFICIAL DOCUMENTATION","","","Submit for Official Release Once your new language/theme is complete and you have throughly tested it on your board, in the community spirit you should submit it for official release through our site so other users can also enjoy it. Zip up the complete language/theme directory (don \'t forget the theme images/ and the spellchecker file for new languages!) with either 7-Zip , WinZip , or WinRar . Attach and send it via Private Message or E-mail , once approved it will be official released on the Fully Modded phpBB site.",1),); ?>